## Week 1 — Day 5 | PostgreSQL Deployment + Full Pipeline

```bash
# Add Bitnami Helm repo
helm repo add bitnami https://charts.bitnami.com/bitnami
helm repo update

# Deploy PostgreSQL into monitoring namespace
helm install postgres bitnami/postgresql --namespace monitoring --set auth.postgresPassword=devops123

# Verify PostgreSQL pod is running
kubectl get pods -n monitoring

# Install Python PostgreSQL driver
pip install psycopg2-binary

# Start all port-forwards with one command
bash start.sh

# Run updated metric fetcher (writes to both CSV and PostgreSQL)
python ml/fetch_metrics.py

# Commit everything
git add .
git commit -m "feat: PostgreSQL deployed, metrics pipeline writing to DB, startup script added"
git push
```

**Port-forwards (via start.sh):**
- Prometheus → http://localhost:9090
- PostgreSQL → localhost:5432
- Grafana → http://localhost:3000

**Result:** 35 rows inserted into `cluster_metrics` table in PostgreSQL. Full pipeline working: Prometheus → Python → CSV + PostgreSQL.

