## Week 2 — Day 1 | CronJob Automation + Docker Hub

```bash
# Check data in PostgreSQL
kubectl exec -it postgres-postgresql-0 -n monitoring -- psql -U postgres
SELECT COUNT(*) FROM cluster_metrics;
SELECT * FROM cluster_metrics ORDER BY timestamp DESC LIMIT 5;
\q

# Build metric fetcher Docker image
cd ml
docker build -t metric-fetcher:latest .
cd ..

# Deploy CronJob into cluster
kubectl apply -f docker/cronjob.yaml

# Verify CronJob is running
kubectl get cronjob -n monitoring

# Check CronJob pods
kubectl get pods -n monitoring | grep metric-fetcher

# Tag and push image to Docker Hub
docker tag metric-fetcher:latest yourusername/metric-fetcher:latest
docker push yourusername/metric-fetcher:latest
```

**Result:** CronJob deployed, firing every 5 minutes. Image pushed to Docker Hub to fix ErrImageNeverPull error.

